  "narrative": "DRIVER\nUSD leads D1+H4 CSM at 100 in a Risk-Off High regime, driven by the US 10Y yield surging 3% to 4.595%, VIX spiking 6.78%, and inflation fear themes dominating news flow. USDCAD is the cleanest expression with D1+H4 both buy, H4 momentum at 70, and CAD accelerating divergence (H4 55 vs D1 33) flagged as the most important short-term signal; USDCHF confirms via its -0.85 EURUSD correlation compressing that pair simultaneously. AUD H4 CSM has collapsed to 26 versus D1 at 65, making AUDUSD an active fade with AUDJPY confirming weakness through its 0.91 correlation.\n\nMOMENTUM\nGaining: USDCAD CMP 60, D1 59 rising, H4 70 rising \u2014 both timeframes aligned long\nFading: EURUSD CMP 37 H4 momentum 13 collapsing; GBPUSD CMP 36 H4 13 decelerating; NZDUSD CMP 43 H4 17 fading hard against D1 63\n\nWATCH\nUS CPI print hits USDJPY directly \u2014 a hot number accelerates the D1+H4 buy signal toward 152 resistance\nCopper extends its 4.23% drop hitting AUDUSD as commodity FX correlation confirms AUD D1 fade accelerates\nSilver down 10.15% tests NZDUSD downside further given NZD CSM sitting at 13 H4, lowest in the board",
